---

#### Summary

The `Array.every()` method is ideal for **verification and validation tasks** in real-world applications.
In this university example, it efficiently checks whether all students meet a condition (`submitted === true`) and ensures data readiness before taking an action (publishing results).

It’s simple, readable, and perfectly suited for any scenario that requires confirming **all items** in an array meet a common requirement.


